.TH MAN_1_SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "April 2024" "Version 1.0" "User Manual"

.SH NAME
man_1_simple_shell \- simple shell program

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B man_1_simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B man_1_simple_shell
program is a simple shell implementation that reads commands from standard input, executes them using the execvp function, and prints the exit status of the executed command.

.SH OPTIONS
This program does not accept any command-line options.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The
.B man_1_simple_shell
program returns the exit status of the last executed command.

.SH ERRORS
If an error occurs during command execution or process creation, an appropriate error message is printed to standard error.

.SH EXAMPLES
To use the
.B man_1_simple_shell
program, compile it with the following command:
.nf
.B gcc -o man_1_simple_shell man_1_simple_shell.c shell.c
.fi
Then, run the program and enter commands to execute:
.nf
.B ./man_1_simple_shell
.fi

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR execvp (3),
.BR fork (2),
.BR waitpid (2),
.BR perror (3)

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Steven Rosario, Luis Soto, Jose Mendez.

.SH BUGS
No known bugs.

